about.summary: Create lots of colorful plots in a plethora of variations. Try the LSD demotour().

name: r-lsd
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "4.0-0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-lsd
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/LSD_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/LSD/LSD_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 038a9cc692c67141da066251110e326faf6e1751dd9b367f4d2c5a9bf91d573b

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 2
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('LSD')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('LSD')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=LSD
  license: Unlimited
  summary: Create lots of colorful plots in a plethora of variations. Try the LSD demotour().
  license_family: OTHER

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
